    "The authors demonstrated that this approach reduced bias by decomposing the max operation in the target function into action selection and evaluation, which improved the update of the action-value function, making it more stable by diminishing the overestimation of the Q-values.",
    "To use parameterized value functions, Double Q-Learning learns two value functions using two different sets of weights Θ and Θ and, at each update step, one set is used to select the action greedily and the other to evaluate it, as defined in Eqs. 18 and 19.",
    "As an agent interacts with stochastic, non-deterministic, and partially observable environments, exploration and exploitation are also essential concepts, and how to balance them is a recurring challenge.",
    "Exploration refers to the experimentation of the new and the generation of new knowledge but tends to maximize risks to expand the agent's knowledge.",
    "Exploitation relates to the knowledge assimilated, the maximization of efficiency and performance, the minimization of risks, and the refinement of the knowledge already acquired."
